  "prompt": "Re the Sochi Olympics online video coverage, if I want to watch an event on streaming video but I cannot watch it live, is there some kind of archive after the event first airs?",
  "response": "Yes, for the Sochi Olympics, there were extensive online video coverage options available, including archives for events after they aired live. Networks like NBC, which had broadcasting rights for the Sochi Olympics, provided replays and highlights of events on their digital platforms. You could access these through NBC's website or app, where they maintained a comprehensive archive of Olympic events. This allowed viewers to watch events at their convenience if they missed the live broadcast.",
